    <node id="IL23R" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="GP130 &amp; IL12RB1 &amp; IL23_e &amp; STAT3 &amp; RORGT"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="hugo:19100"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Activated by its subchain(s) and by its associated cytokine(s) (external or secreted).

Activated by Rorgt: functional data in Zhou et al. (2007) (Fig 1B).

Activated by Stat3: functional data in Zhou et al. (2007) (Fig 5C).

STAT3- or RORgt- Th cells fails to activate IL23R (see Fig.1A, 1B, 5B and 5C in Zhou et al., 2007). This suggests a synergic activation of IL23R by STAT3 and RORgt.</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="552" y="182" style="Node style 8"/>
    </node>
